Specify a unique request ID so that if you must retry your request, the server will know to ignore the request if it has already been completed. The server will guarantee that for at least 60 minutes since the first request. For example, consider a situation where you make an initial request and the request times out. If you make the request again with the same request ID, the server can check if original operation with the same request ID was received, and if so, will ignore the second request. cancel.description: Starts asynchronous cancellation on a long-running operation. The server makes a best effort to cancel the operation, but success is not guaranteed. If the server doesn't support this method, it returns `google.rpc.Code.UNIMPLEMENTED`. Clients can use Operations.GetOperation or other methods to check whether the cancellation succeeded or whether the operation completed despite cancellation. On successful cancellation, the operation is not deleted; instead, it becomes an operation with an Operation.error value with a google.rpc.Status.code of 1, corresponding to `Code.CANCELLED`.

CloneJob.description: CloneJob describes the process of creating a clone of a MigratingVM to the requested target based on the latest successful uploaded snapshots. While the migration cycles of a MigratingVm take place, it is possible to verify the uploaded VM can be started in the cloud, by creating a clone. The clone can be created without any downtime, and it is created using the latest snapshots which are already in the cloud. The cloneJob is only responsible for its work, not its products, which means once it is finished, it will never touch the instance it created. It will only delete it in case of the CloneJob being cancelled or upon failure to clone.

For other methods, the response should have the type `XxxResponse`, where `Xxx` is the original method name. If you make the request again with the same request ID, the server can check if original operation with the same request ID was received, and if so, will ignore the second request. This prevents clients from accidentally creating duplicate commitments. The request ID must be a valid UUID with the exception that zero UUID is not supported (00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000).

UtilizationReport.description: Utilization report details the utilization (CPU, memory, etc.) of selected source VMs.

createTime.description: Output only. The time the report was created (this refers to the time of the request, not the time the report creation completed).

displayName.description: The report display name, as assigned by the user.

error.description: Output only. Provides details on the state of the report in case of an error.

frameEndTime.description: Output only. The point in time when the time frame ends. Notice that the time frame is counted backwards. For instance if the "frame_end_time" value is 2021/01/20 and the time frame is WEEK then the report covers the week between 2021/01/20 and 2021/01/14.

name.description: Output only. The report unique name.

state.description: Output only. Current state of the report.
enumDescriptions: The state is unknown. This value is not in use.
The report is in the making.
Report creation completed successfully.
Report creation failed.

stateTime.description: Output only. The time the state was last set.

enumDescriptions: The time frame was not specified and will default to WEEK.
One week.
One month.
One year.

vmCount.description: Output only. Total number of VMs included in the report.

vms.description: List of utilization information per VM. When sent as part of the request, the "vm_id" field is used in order to specify which VMs to include in the report. In that case all other fields are ignored.

vmsCount.description: Output only. Total number of VMs included in the report.

VmUtilizationInfo.description: Utilization information of a single VM.

vmId.description: The VM's ID in the source.

vmwareVmDetails.description: The description of the VM in a Source of type Vmware.

VmUtilizationMetrics.description: Utilization metrics values for a single VM.

diskIoRateAverage.description: Average disk IO rate, in kilobytes per second.

diskIoRateAverageKbps.description: Average disk IO rate, in kilobytes per second.

diskIoRateMax.description: Max disk IO rate, in kilobytes per second.

diskIoRateMaxKbps.description: Max disk IO rate, in kilobytes per second.

networkThroughputAverage.description: Average network throughput (combined transmit-rates and receive-rates), in kilobytes per second.

networkThroughputAverageKbps.description: Average network throughput (combined transmit-rates and receive-rates), in kilobytes per second.

networkThroughputMax.description: Max network throughput (combined transmit-rates and receive-rates), in kilobytes per second.

networkThroughputMaxKbps.description: Max network throughput (combined transmit-rates and receive-rates), in kilobytes per second.

VmwareSourceDetails.description: VmwareSourceDetails message describes a specific source details for the vmware source type.

password.description: Input only. The credentials password. This is write only and can not be read in a GET operation.

thumbprint.description: The thumbprint representing the certificate for the vcenter.

vcenterIp.description: The ip address of the vcenter this Source represents.

VmwareVmDetails.description: VmwareVmDetails describes a VM in vCenter.

bootOption.description: Output only. The VM Boot Option.
enumDescriptions: The boot option is unknown.
The boot option is EFI.
The boot option is BIOS.

committedStorage.description: The total size of the storage allocated to the VM in MB.

committedStorageMb.description: The total size of the storage allocated to the VM in MB.

cpuCount.description: The number of cpus in the VM.

datacenterDescription.description: The descriptive name of the vCenter's datacenter this VM is contained in.

datacenterId.description: The id of the vCenter's datacenter this VM is contained in.

diskCount.description: The number of disks the VM has.

displayName.description: The display name of the VM. Note that this is not necessarily unique.

guestDescription.description: The VM's OS. See for example https://vdc-repo.vmware.com/vmwb-repository/dcr-public/da47f910-60ac-438b-8b9b-6122f4d14524/16b7274a-bf8b-4b4c-a05e-746f2aa93c8c/doc/vim.vm.GuestOsDescriptor.GuestOsIdentifier.html for types of strings this might hold.

memoryMb.description: The size of the memory of the VM in MB.

powerState.description: The power state of the VM at the moment list was taken.
enumDescriptions: Power state is not specified.
The VM is turned ON.
The VM is turned OFF.
The VM is suspended. This is similar to hibernation or sleep mode.

uuid.description: The unique identifier of the VM in vCenter.

vmId.description: The VM's id in the source (note that this is not the MigratingVm's id). This is the moref id of the VM.

details.description: The details of the vmware VMs.

title: VM Migration API
